2.title: Making Friends
2.plot: The Teletubbies say 'eh-oh' to each other in turn and then say 'eh-oh' to flowers whilst the children in Tummy Tales make a friendship circle out of handprints.

23.title: Train Ride
23.plot: When Po goes on the Tubby Custard Ride it makes lots of Tubby Custard - too much for Po to eat alone. So, Po choo-choos off to get Tinky Winky, Dipsy and Laa-Laa so all of the Teletubbies can share the Tubby Custard. In Tummy Tales, children take a ride on a steam train.

24.title: Wait for It
24.plot: The Teletubbies wait for Tubby Toast, then they wait for the Tubby Phone to be answered and finally they wait to see the Tiddlytubbies go to Sleepybyes. A boy in Tummy Tales waits to cross a road with his Grandad and waits for a bus.

25.title: Snowball
25.plot: It's a cold day in Teletubbyland and snow falls on the Teletubbies. They find big snowballs, dance with a snowman and watch children make a caterpillar from snow. Tinky Winky puts Dipsy's hat in the bag and then The Noo-noo hoovers them both up. Children in Tummy Tales pack a bag for an overnight stay with a relative and the Teletubbies do a suitcase dance.

26.title: Packing
26.plot: Tinky Winky puts Dipsy's hat in the bag and then The Noo-noo hoovers them both up. Children in Tummy Tales pack a bag for an overnight stay with a relative and the Teletubbies do a suitcase dance.

27.title: Number Four
27.plot: The Teletubbies count to four - four Teletubbies, four flowers, four pieces of Tubby Toast. In Tummy Tales, two sisters help Dad put up a number four on the front door of their house.

28.title: Flying
28.plot: The Teletubbies pretend to fly and children in Tummy Tales enjoy watching flying swans. Po goes so fast on the scooter that it takes off and flies over Teletubbyland!

29.title: Taps
29.plot: Tinky Winky's bag fills with sparkles from a tap and Home Dome overflows with Tubby Custard until Po turns the Tubby Custard Machine off. A child in Tummy Tales uses a new tap in the bathroom when she brushes her teeth before bedtime.

30.title: Party!
30.plot: It's party time: the Teletubbies have balloons, party blowers and lots of sparkles. They visit the Tiddlytubbies and do a fun party dance. In Tummy Tales, twins celebrate their birthday party with all of their friends.

31.title: Custard Chaos
31.plot: The Tubby Custard Machine careers crazily out of Home Dome and goes on a messy Tubby Custard Ride around Teletubbyland with all four Teletubbies on board. The Noo-noo cleans up Home Dome and the rain washes away the custard splodges on the hills. A boy in Tummy Tales makes custard with his Dad.

32.title: Tallest Shortest
32.plot: The Teletubbies are standing up straight to see who is the tallest and who is the shortest. Tinky Winky and Po play 'Tallest, Shortest' with the Tiddlytubbies and the children in Tummy Tales put themselves in height order ready for a photograph to be taken.

33.title: Rolling
33.plot: Laa-Laa and Po have fun first rolling a ball down a hill and then rolling each other down the hill. The Teletubbies enjoy watching children have fun rolling slowly down slopes too.

34.title: Conga
34.plot: The Teletubbies do conga dances over the hills, then they conga into Home Dome to answer the Tubby Phone and do a special conga Tubby Phone Dance. In Tummy Tales, children have lots of fun as they conga around a soft play centre.

35.title: Waving
35.plot: After a fun waving game with the Tiddlytubbies, the Teletubbies enjoy watching children waving as they set off on a short boat trip. Finally the Teletubbies wave to the Tiddlytubbies who are off to Sleepybyes.

36.title: Catch the Ball
36.plot: The Teletubbies play with a bubble and then Po and Laa-Laa play catch with a ball. In Tummy Tales, two brothers learn to catch a ball and play catch with their dog.

37.title: Loop the Loop
37.plot: In Tummy Tales, a group of children watch a plane loop-the-loop in the air, whilst the Teletubbies have magical fun watching a shooting star loop-the-loop. Later, the Tubby Toast goes loop-the-loop too as it flies out of the Tubby Toaster.

38.title: Follow the Leader
38.plot: The Teletubbies play choo-choo and follow the Tubby Custard Machine on a Tubby Custard Ride. In Tummy Tales, children follow their nursery teacher to the local playground.

39.title: Purple
39.plot: In Tummy Tales, a boy learns to knit with purple wool and in Teletubbyland, purple Tinky Winky answers the Tubby Phone and leads the Tubby Phone Dance. Tinky Winky also plays with the Tiddlytubbies.

40.title: Ballet
40.plot: Dipsy ballet twirls with the Tiddlytubbies and the children in Tummy Tales put on a ballet show for their family at home.

41.title: Taking a Ride
41.plot: The Teletubbies ride the Dup Dup and the Tubby Custard Machine takes them on a Tubby Custard Ride. In Tummy Tales, a boy takes a ride on a cable car.

42.title: Photos
42.plot: The Teletubbies take selfies with the Tubby Phone and a child in Tummy Tales has their photo taken in a photo booth with their grandparent. Then it's time for a Tubby Phone Dance.

43.title: Knock Knock
43.plot: Tinky Winky knock-knocks on a door and is welcomed by Dipsy, Laa-Laa and Po. The children in Tummy Tales knock-knock on their neighbours' doors to share their home-made flapjacks. The Teletubbies have more knock-knock fun with the Tiddlytubbies.

44.title: Things
44.plot: The Teletubbies find different uses for their favourite things and a child in Tummy Tales makes a seaside picture out of lots of things from a make-and-do box. In Teletubbyland a large tube appears. The Teletubbies use it as a telescope and as a loud speaker.

45.title: Breakfast
45.plot: It's breakfast time for the children in Tummy Tales and in Teletubbyland, the Teletubbies wake up and can't decide whether to have Tubby Custard or Tubby Toast - so they have both!

46.title: Keep Fit
46.plot: The Teletubbies feel tired after doing lots of keep fit exercises but they are ready for action again after eating lots of Tubby Custard. In Tummy Tales, a child, her Mum and their dog keep fit on a beach.

47.title: Party Invitation
47.plot: In Tummy Tales, a child makes party invitations and in Teletubbyland a magical party invitation arrives. It's an invitation for the Teletubbies to attend the Tiddlytubbies' party.

48.title: Taking Turns
48.plot: Laa-Laa and Po take turns to ride Po's scooter and then they take turns to play with the Tiddlytubbies. Children in Tummy Tales take turns to press apples into juice.

49.title: Horses
49.plot: Tinky Winky, Dipsy and Laa-Laa trot and gallop across Teletubbyland pretending to be horses. Children in Tummy Tales help to groom and feed a horse.

50.title: Running Race
50.plot: The Teletubbies do running races and they each have a chance to win. When the Tubby Phone rings, there's a race to reach it before the Tubby Phone Dance. In Tummy Tales, two sisters watch their Dad running in a race.

51.title: Fixing Things
51.plot: The Tubby Custard Machine is broken but The Noo-noo fixes it. The Teletubbies go on a Tubby Custard Ride and make a lovely custardy mess inside and outside Home Dome. In Tummy Tales, a boy helps his Mum fix a hole in his space hopper.

52.title: Being Quiet
52.plot: Tinky Winky can't sleep and goes outside to play so as not to wake the other Teletubbies. But Tinky Winky's noisy footsteps, on top of Home Dome, wakes them up! In Tummy Tales, children quietly feed some birds and the Teletubbies are quiet as they watch the Tiddlytubbies go to Sleepybyes.

53.title: Music
53.plot: The Teletubbies become a pop group and perform a pop song. In Tummy Tales, children watch a one man band playing music and accompany him by playing their own music.

54.title: Making Sounds
54.plot: Po makes lots of silly, funny sounds with the levers and buttons in Home Dome and then the Tubby Phone rings for a silly Tubby Phone Dance. The Teletubbies enjoy watching children visit a farm and copying the sounds they hear.

55.title: Rainbow
55.plot: The Teletubbies go for a walk on a lovely sunny day but then clouds appear and it starts to rain. A rainbow shines in the sky and a rainbow path gives the Teletubbies a magical trail to follow. In Tummy Tales, children make a huge rainbow print with their feet.

56.title: Twinkle Twinkle
56.plot: It is night time in Teletubbyland and the Teletubbies are all sleeping, apart from Tinky Winky. Stepping outside, Tinky Winky sees a star in the sky which sings 'Twinkle Twinkle". The other Teletubbies are woken so, they can enjoy the special twinkly star. In Tummy Tales, a girl looks up to the night sky to spot the twinkliest star.

57.title: Football
57.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

58.title: Again Again
58.plot: The Teletubbies can't get enough of the Tubby Custard Ride so they ask to go on it again and again! In Tummy Tales, children play on a slide again and again.

59.title: Tall Tower
59.plot: Laa-Laa has fun watching Dipsy stretch up, like a very tall tower. The Tubby Toaster goes crazy and fires out lots of Tubby Toast which ends up in a tall tower too. The Teletubbies watch children climb the stairs to the top of a tall tower in Tummy Tales.

60.title: Inside Outside
60.plot: The Teletubbies have lots of fun playing inside and outside Home Dome. They wave to the Tiddlytubbies from inside AND outside too. In Tummy Tales, a girl helps her Dad take wet washing from inside to hang up outside to dry.

-1.title: Big Dance
-1.plot: As the children in Tummy Tales dance together on a colourful dance floor which lights up, the Teletubbies do a new dance, first in pairs and then all together.
